  <brief_title>Clown Doctors and a Sedative Premedicant for Children Undergoing Surgery</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Shaare Zedek Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Shaare Zedek Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the present investigation will be to determine whether a combination of clown
      doctor and parental presence is more effective than a combination of sedative premedication
      and parental presence for reducing anxiety in children and their parents and for improving
      parental satisfaction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
